-- Brazil’s Embraer Opens Factories in Portugal, RTP Reports
-- B y   G a b r i e l l e   C o p p o l a
-- 2012-09-22T13:49:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-22/brazil-s-embraer-opens-factories-in-portugal-rtp-reports.html
Embraer SA (EMBR3) , the world’s fourth-
biggest planemaker, opened two new factories in Evora, Portugal,
broadcaster RTP  reported  on its website yesterday, citing
company president Frederico Curado.  Embraer invested 177 million euros ($230 million) in the
two factories, which will make airplane components.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gabrielle Coppola in Sao Paulo at 
 gcoppola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  